This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes an end-to-end approach for printed text OCR. It also involves image processing and feature extraction techniques. 

It could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves sequence to sequence learning for text prediction and retrieval. 

The paper also involves deep learning techniques such as LSTMs, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper proposes a method for text retrieval, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
